        <Summary>Nested Imports for Python</Summary>
        <Description>python-nimp installs a harmless meta import-hook that adds support for nested packages, i.e., multiple packages that "live" under a common namespace. This is the idiom in Java, where you have packages like com.foo.bar.spam and com.foo.bar.eggs, as well as in Haskell and several other languages.</Description>
